  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/6232",
  "title": "Headers are being used in client component",
  "body": "### 🐛 Current behavior\n\nusing version 0.3,1 that is an update here: [https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/6223/commits/bbb8c2a777a807da9ab7308f1f0c41c7ad4dae6e](here)\r\n\r\nI see headers are being used in client component: https://nextjs.org/docs/app/api-reference/functions/headers\r\n\r\nThis causes issues when running locally:\r\n\r\n![image](https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/assets/13868698/94f21e15-7ce8-47ad-9a55-7ddfc9067f00)\r\n\r\nmore info about this issue why headers is out of context here: [link](https://nextjs.org/docs/messages/next-dynamic-api-wrong-context)\r\n\n\n### 🔍 Steps to reproduce\n\nrunning locally, when calling an actions or revalidating.\n\n### Live reproduction\n\nhttp://localhost:3000\n\n### 💭 Expected behavior\n\nNo headers issue breaking dev \n\n### Package version\n\nreact-instantsearch-nextjs 0.3.1\n\n### Operating system\n\nWindows\n\n### Browser\n\nChrome\n\n### Code of Conduct\n\n- [X] I agree to follow this project's Code of Conduct",
